# FoxLAP DIY GPS Lap Timer  
**Built with Adafruit Feather ESP32 V2 ‚Äì Optimized for Efficiency, Performance & Assembly**

This is a DIY open-source GPS lap timer designed for track day enthusiasts and data nerds. With a compact footprint, built-in battery charging, high-speed GPS logging, and SD data capture, this project gives you timing accuracy without expensive hardware.

---

## Features

- Fast 10Hz GPS for precise lap timing
- OLED screen for real-time lap display
- MicroSD logging for full post-session analysis
- Rechargeable 3.7V LiPo battery w/ USB-C charging
- Compact and 3D printable housing
- Easily hackable with CircuitPython or Arduino

