‚∏ª

Wiring Overview
	‚Ä¢	Feather ESP32 V2 to GPS: UART TX/RX
	‚Ä¢	OLED via SPI (SCK, MOSI, DC, CS, RST)
	‚Ä¢	SD via SPI (shared bus with OLED, separate CS)
	‚Ä¢	Buttons to GPIOs with pull-up resistors
	‚Ä¢	Battery plugs into Feather JST connector (auto-charging)
	‚Ä¢	Switch optionally connected to Feather EN for hard power cutoff

‚∏ª

Powering On / Charging
	1.	Plug in USB-C to charge the battery and/or upload firmware
	2.	Disconnect USB to run fully on battery
	3.	Toggle switch to power on/off (optional but recommended)

‚∏ª

Optional Upgrades
	‚Ä¢	Add BLE lap beacon triggers using Feather BLE capabilities
	‚Ä¢	Add G-sensor via I2C or analog input
	‚Ä¢	Add NeoPixel strip or ring for lap/impact indication

